      "content": "i know they care but that's the problem. their care is just constant stress for them. i see it in their faces every day. if i'm gone, that stress just... disappears instantly. isn't it more logical to look at the actual impact i'm having instead of just feelings? like, mathematically, if i'm a net negative to their well being, wouldn't removing the negative make things better for them?",
